<paragraph blockId="34.[192,1440,1677,1929]" lastBlockId="35.[192,1440,217,337]" lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,1677,1701]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Definition.</emphasis>
A possible sister to 
<taxonomicName authority="Scudder, 1872" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1872" box="[600,910,1677,1702]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Cymaenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[600,723,1678,1701]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Cymaenes</emphasis>
Scudder, 1872
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[928,982,1678,1702]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" authorityYear="1865" box="[1089,1326,1677,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Cobalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tripunctus">
<emphasis box="[1089,1326,1677,1701]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Cobalus tripunctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Herrich- Schäffer, 1865) and far removed from 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1955" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1955" box="[670,913,1710,1734]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Vidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[670,750,1710,1734]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Vidius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[760,913,1710,1734]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans, 1955</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[931,985,1710,1734]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1891" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1891" box="[1090,1431,1710,1734]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Narga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vidius">
<emphasis box="[1090,1253,1710,1734]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Narga vidius</emphasis>
Mabille, 1891
</taxonomicName>
) where it was placed previously (
<figureCitation box="[594,728,1742,1766]" captionStart-0="Figure 11" captionStart-1="Figure 12" captionStartId-0="29.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionStartId-1="31.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox-0="[195,1438,214,1295]" captionTargetBox-1="[194,1440,214,1295]" captionTargetId-0="figure@29.[194,1442,213,1296]" captionTargetId-1="figure@31.[192,1440,213,1296]" captionTargetPageId-0="29" captionTargetPageId-1="31" captionText-0="Figure 11. Nuclear genome and Z chromosome trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." captionText-1="Figure 12. Mitochondrial genome and COI barcode trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677257" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677259" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3677257/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3677259/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Fig. 11–12</figureCitation>
). Keys to J. 
<quantity box="[869,960,1742,1766]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.1214" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" unit="in" value="24.1">24.1 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[969,1136,1742,1766]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans (1955)</bibRefCitation>
. Genitalia illustrated by Mielke in his fig. 5–8 (
<bibRefCitation author="Mielke" box="[466,622,1775,1799]" firstAuthor="Mielke" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" pagination="127 - 172" refId="ref27880" refString="Mielke, O. H. H. 1980. Contribuicao ao estudo faunistico dos Hesperiidae americanos. VI. Nota suplementar as especies de Hesperiinae do Rio Grande do Sul, Brasil (Lepidoptera). Acta Biologica Paranaense 8 - 9: 127 - 172." type="journal article" year="1980">Mielke 1980</bibRefCitation>
). Distinguished from its relatives by antennae shorter than half of costa length, wings rounded, broad, scales in fringes long, especially on forewing, nearly the same as palpi in length, wings almost entirely unmarked, chocolate brown, in some specimens, wings below with faint, blotchy yellowish spots consisting of a few scales and forming postdiscal bands and a discal cell spot on hindwing. Valva narrow, ~2-3 times longer than wide, harpe distally slightly to moderately upturned not well-separated from valva, costa of valva straight, uncus narrowly divided, arms short, close together, gnathos the same length as uncus, saccus as long as tegumen with uncus, penis narrow, twice as long as saccus. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly2096.50.1:A1451C, aly349.40.1:A898C, aly164.63.12:C436A, aly164.63.12:A437T, aly5965.2.3:C1150G.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="34" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="35.[192,1440,361,418]" pageId="35" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,361,385]" pageId="35" pageNumber="34">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a masculine noun in the nominative singular. It is a fusion of the 
<typeStatus box="[1295,1348,362,386]" pageId="35" pageNumber="34">type</typeStatus>
species name with its original genus name: 
<emphasis box="[633,676,393,417]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="34">Fid</emphasis>
[o] + [Vid] 
<emphasis box="[797,834,394,417]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="34">ius</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[192,1116,441,466]" box="[192,1116,441,466]" pageId="35" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,432,441,465]" pageId="35" pageNumber="34">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[493,546,442,466]" pageId="35" pageNumber="34">type</typeStatus>
species and 
<taxonomicName authority="O. Mielke, 1980" authorityName="O. Mielke" authorityYear="1980" box="[701,1113,441,466]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Vidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochraceus">
<emphasis box="[701,909,441,465]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="34">Vidius ochraceus</emphasis>
O. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mielke" box="[951,1113,441,466]" firstAuthor="Mielke" pageId="35" pageNumber="34" pagination="127 - 172" refId="ref27880" refString="Mielke, O. H. H. 1980. Contribuicao ao estudo faunistico dos Hesperiidae americanos. VI. Nota suplementar as especies de Hesperiinae do Rio Grande do Sul, Brasil (Lepidoptera). Acta Biologica Paranaense 8 - 9: 127 - 172." type="journal article" year="1980">Mielke, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[192,822,489,514]" box="[192,822,489,514]" pageId="35" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,380,489,513]" pageId="35" pageNumber="34">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Subtribe Moncina A. 
<bibRefCitation author="Warren, A. D. &amp; J. R. Ogawa &amp; A. V. Z. Brower" box="[647,819,490,514]" journalOrPublisher="Phylogenetic relationships of subfamilies and circumscription of tribes in the family Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea). Cladistics" pageId="35" pageNumber="34" pagination="642 - 676" part="24" refId="ref28580" refString="Warren, A. D., J. R. Ogawa, and A. V. Z. Brower. 2008. Phylogenetic relationships of subfamilies and circumscription of tribes in the family Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea). Cladistics 24 (5): 642 - 676." type="journal article" year="2008">Warren, 2008</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
